================================================================================
DATA PROVENANCE
================================================================================

`DataFiles/featureTable.mat` is a derived product built from:

1. **Copernicus Marine Environment Monitoring Service (CMEMS) Black Sea
   reanalysis and analysis/forecast** — physical fields used as environmental
   predictors (temperature, salinity, density, currents, sea-surface height,
   mixed-layer depth). Two products:
     - Black Sea Physics Reanalysis — DOI: https://doi.org/10.48670/mds-00356
     - Black Sea Physics Analysis and Forecast — DOI: https://doi.org/10.48670/mds-00355
   Subject to the CMEMS license, which permits redistribution of derived
   products with attribution. See: https://marine.copernicus.eu/

2. **Argo BGC float profiles** — dissolved oxygen and supporting
   measurements as the regression target. The Argo snapshot
   (DOI 10.17882/42182) is published under the Creative Commons
   Attribution 4.0 (CC-BY 4.0) license. These data were collected and
   made freely available by the international Argo project and the
   national programs that contribute to it. The Argo Program is part
   of the Global Ocean Observing System.
   See: https://argo.ucsd.edu/ — DOI: https://doi.org/10.17882/42182

`DepthWeights.mat` is a 2 KB precomputed lookup of per-depth oxygen
standard deviations used to assign sample weights in the depth-weighted
Random CV variants. It was computed from the development set of
`featureTable.mat`.

